Organisation Name: NHS Arden and Greater East Midlands Commissioning Support Unit
Title: Integrated Care Provider (ICP) Consultancy Service
Description:
This Procurement has established a Supplier Contract(s) for the purchase of a consultancy service to assist the CCG  with the information required to make an informed decision regarding the development of an Integrated Care Partnership (ICP) within Milton Keynes. 

The method used to acquire preferred bidder(s) was a compliant process under the Public Contracts Regulations 2015 ("PCR") using a further competition under the Crown Commercial Service Management Consultancy Framework Two - RM6008 framework -Lot 3. The contract will be for an initial period of August - November 2019 with extension clauses included that may or may not be utilised as follows;
6 months after the above end date or 12 months after the above end date

Any extension clause will be enacted without further competition and award will be completely at the discretion of the Authority(s).

The highest value given includes all possible extension periods

Correct signature date is 16th September 2019, other date included to allow notice publish only.

Title: PROVISION OF CONSULTANCY SUPPORT FOR THE KENT AND MEDWAY STROKE REVIEW  DECISION MAKING BUSINESS CASE (DMBC)
Description:
This Procurement was to establish a Supplier Contract for the provision of Consultancy Support for the Kent and Medway Stroke Review Decision Making Business Case ( DMBC ).
The contract will be for an initial 6 month period with an option to extend for up to a further 6 months if required.
This Contract will be between the successful Supplier and the Authority. 
The Contract has been awarded under the Crown Commercial Service Management Consultancy - RM3745 Lot 5 Framework agreement.  The Terms and Conditions of this framework will govern any resultant Contract.
Contact Name: NHS Commercial Solutions on behalf of the Commissioners

Title: Management Consultancy Phase 1 Award
Description:
Crown Commercial Service as the Authority has put in place a Pan Government Collaborative Framework Agreement for use by UK public sector bodies identified at VI.3 (and any future successors to these organisations), which include Central Government Departments and their Arm's Length Bodies and Agencies, Non Departmental Public Bodies, NHS bodies and Local Authorities. This Procurement shall establish a multi Supplier public sector Framework Agreement for the purchase of Management Consultancy Services. This Framework Agreement shall comprise of 2 Lots. The Authority reserves the right for an electronic auction to be held by Contracting Authorities during further competition prior to an award of a contract.
Potential Providers have the opportunity to bid for all or any combination of the Lots.
Contact Address 1: 9th Floor, The Capital Building, Old Hall Street

Organisation Name: HealthTrust Europe LLP (HTE) acting as agent for the University Hospitals of Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust ("UHCW")
Title: Consultancy and Advisory Services
Description: HealthTrust Europe sought to establish a framework agreement for the supply of Consultancy and Advisory Services. The scope of this framework agreement includes provision of Consultancy and Advisory Services in a number of disciplines which will normally include providing the customer with a delivery programme, mobilisation and communication plan with agreed milestones and delivery dates. The requirements are for provision of advice and options rather than to make business decisions on the customer's behalf although customers may invite providers' input in making final decisions.
